<HEADLINE>
<P>
BENEFITS OF RIDE-SHARING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Warner Center's innovative ride-sharing incentive package is great news for 
Warner Center employees and local residents alike. It should significantly 
reduce the number of cars in and around Warner Center. I'm glad The Times 
featured this new program so prominently (June 16). 
</P>
<P>
The ride-sharing program and incentives are part of a comprehensive plan to 
relieve traffic congestion in Warner Center. I created the city's Warner Center 
Trust Fund to finance this plan, using $5.5 million assessed of local developer 
Robert Voit. My office is developing the traffic improvement plan with the city 
Department of Transportation and Warner Center businesses. 
</P>
<P>
The city already requires future developers to be responsible for easing 
traffic. The trust fund is a first because it also targets developers of 
existing projects. 
</P>
<P>
We're making ride-sharing as easy, stress-free and financially attractive as 
possible. The incentive package includes fare subsidies for the first three 
months, and a free month's fare after 11 months participation in a van pool or 
bus pool. The "Guaranteed Ride Home" service provides a free ride home for 
ride-sharing employees who have unexpected work or family emergencies during 
the workday. With the hot weather and smog upon us, now's the time to jump into 
the pool: the car, bus or van pool! 
</P>
<P>
JOY PICUS 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
<P>
 Picus is city councilwoman for the 3rd District. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
