<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: WOMAN FOUND IN FIELD WAS STABBED TO DEATH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An autopsy on the body of a woman found in a field in Pacoima determined that 
she had been stabbed to death, Los Angeles police said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
The badly decomposed body was found by a security guard walking to work Sunday 
morning in a field off Osborne Street near the Hansen Dam Recreation Center, 
Detective Al Ferrand said. An autopsy was completed Thursday, and medical 
examiners found multiple stab wounds, he said. 
</P>
<P>
There were no suspects, and investigators had been unable to identify the 
victim. She was described as black, 20 to 35 years old, wearing a black jacket, 
and a pink and black shirt with matching shorts. 
</P>
<P>
Ferrand said detectives were unable to match her description with reports of 
missing women. He said investigators suspect that the woman was killed in the 
field rather than dumped there. 
</P>
</TEXT>
