<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: PAROLEE ARRESTED IN SHOOTING INCIDENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 38-year-old parolee was arrested about 3 p.m. Friday after his Sylmar 
neighbors complained that he was firing a gun, Los Angeles police said. 
</P>
<P>
Police Lt. George Rock said Steven Dasovich, who lives at the house in the 
15000 block of Paddock Street where he was arrested, was booked on suspicion of 
being an ex-convict in possession of a firearm, a felony. 
</P>
<P>
Rock said Dasovich was on parole from the state Department of Corrections on a 
charge of possessing a dangerous weapon. He was being held at the Van Nuys Jail 
without bail because of the parole violation. 
</P>
<P>
Dasovich fired the sawed-off shotgun at least three times before police entered 
his home and arrested him without incident, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Neighbors said Dasovich had been drinking the previous night and had also 
disturbed the neighborhood by firing the shotgun. No one was injured by the 
gunshots either Friday or the night before, Rock said. 
