<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: FIREBOMB TOSSED IN HOUSE; WOMAN HURT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An Altadena woman suffered second- and third-degree burns over most of her body 
early Friday morning after a Molotov cocktail tossed through her bedroom window 
set her single-story home ablaze, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Cennie Elaine Earby, 34, suffered burns over 90% of her body when her home at 
578 W. Palm St. was firebombed about 2:15 a.m., a spokesman for the Los Angeles 
County Sheriff's Department said. 
</P>
<P>
Nine people in the home escaped unharmed. 
</P>
<P>
Earby was airlifted to Huntington Memorial Hospital in Pasadena and, hours 
later, flown to the Sherman Oaks Burn Center. Earby, who Sheriff's Department 
spokesmen said was dragged from the house by three unnamed people, is listed in 
critical condition at the burn center. 
</P>
<P>
Department spokesmen said they suspect that the bombing may have been in 
retaliation for an earlier, undisclosed gang-related incident. 
</P>
