<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Fixed Mortgage Rates Keep Dipping: Thirty-year fixed-rate home mortgages are 
averaging 10.07%, according to a national survey released by the Federal Home 
Loan Mortgage Corp. That rate was down from a rate of 10.19% last week. 
Adjustable-rate mortgages averaged 8.92%, down from 9.0% last week. The 
fixed-rate average is for a 30-year loan covering 80% of a home's cost. The 
average adjustable-rate mortgage also is for 30 years but for 75% of the home 
price. 
</P>
