<P>
Bond Appeals Panel's Ruling: Lawyers for Australian millionaire Alan Bond 
appealed a tribunal's ruling that said he was unfit to run his nationwide media 
network. Bond Media, which runs radio and television stations, applied to the 
Federal Court to overturn a ruling by the Australian Broadcasting Tribunal that 
Bond is "not fit and proper" to have a broadcasting license. The ruling, due in 
part to Alan Bond's negotiation of a large defamation settlement with a leading 
politician and his alleged attempts to cover up that payment, could force the 
divestment of a network bought for more than $750 million. 
