<TEXT>
<P>
Higher Bid for Gateway Corp.: A group headed by Wasserstein Perella &amp; Co. 
has raised its bid for the British food store chain Gateway Corp. by $71 
million in an effort to defeat an offer from rival Isosceles PLC. The New York 
investment firm and its partner, Great Atlantic &amp; Pacific Tea Co., offered 
$3.75 a share, up from $3.67. The new offer is worth about $3.34 billion. The 
bidders, operating under the name Newgateway, said this was their final offer. 
While the bid exceeds the $3.56-a-share cash portion of the Isosceles' offer, 
it falls short of the $3.79 to $3.87 a share that Isosceles' advisers claim 
their cash-and-stock bid is worth. 
