<HEADLINE>
<P>
GARDENING; 
</P>
<P>
WEEKEND CHECKLIST FOR DEDICATED DIGGERS AND PLANTERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
For dedicated gardeners, here are suggestions from the California Assn. of 
Nurserymen: 
</P>
<P>
Feed vegetables periodically with a mild, balanced fertilizer for bigger and 
better harvests. 
</P>
<P>
Many insects are at their peak during hot weather. Consult a nurseryman for 
tips on controlling aphids, cutworms, white flies, ants, earwigs and snails. 
</P>
<P>
If berry vines have finished producing, cut off the old canes that bore fruit 
this year and loosely twine new growth onto the trellis. 
</P>
<P>
Now is an excellent time to plant almost anything from containers or flats, 
just don't let the plants dry out before or after planting. A little Vitamin 
B-1 will help them overcome the transplanting shock. 
</P>
</TEXT>
