<HEADLINE>
<P>
ART MUSEUM FILLS VACANCY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CATHY CURTIS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Lucinda A. Barnes has been named associate curator at the Newport Harbor Art 
Museum, replacing Anne Ayres who left the museum last year to become director 
of the art gallery at the Otis Art Institute of the Parsons School of Design in 
Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
Barnes has been curator of exhibitions at the Cal State Long Beach University 
Art Museum since 1985. Her previous positions include director of the Karl 
Bornstein Gallery in Santa Monica, and research assistant in the 20th-Century 
Art Department of the Los Angeles County Museum of Art. 
</P>
<P>
Barnes, who is completing her doctorate at the University of Southern 
California, holds a bachelor of arts degree from New York University and a 
master of arts in art history from Williams College. She has taught art history 
at Cal State Fullerton, Saddleback College, UC Irvine Extension and UCLA 
Extension. She assumes her new post Oct 1. CATHY CURTIS 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
NEWPORT HARBOR ART MUSEUM; MANAGEMENT 
</P>
